replies.body:
> AP defensive options: {{item:3157}} {{item:3102}} 


Ummmmm you're forgetting a ton that give HP {{item:3027}} {{item:3152}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3030}} {{item:3116}} 


{{item:3040}} also has a large shield

Still, all of them have lower AP and are extremely situational on a lot of AP mages. 
RoA: 4/5 mages build it regularly and takes 10 min to stack;
Protobelt: I think that it's only core on Vlad and AP Kennen, not worth it imo;
Liandry: good item but wasted money if the enemies aren't stacking HP;
GLP: they could call it "Aurelion Sol's only item" because he's the only champion that often builds it;
Rylai: decent choice for kite mages and it was nerfed because it was as good as old Zhonyas;
Archangel: needs a lot of time to stack, gives low stats early game, has a very high cooldown and it's super situational.

All of those items have HP = defense, yes, but they're not overbearing or give stupid amounts of defense for no trade off. All of them have worse stats than AP only items, thing that items like PD or DD don't necessarily lose.
